Module com.example.project3
Package oitkmg.project3

Class GymManagerController

java.lang.Object
oitkmg.project3.GymManagerController
public class GymManagerController extends Object
Class used to handle the member database, class schedule, and the events of the GUI. Interactions with the GUI are handled in this class.
Author:
Kevin George, Omar Talaat

      private String printFitnessClassSchedule()

      a String representing the fitness class schedule.

      Returns:
      a string representing the fitness class' members and guests.

    • removeMember

      private void removeMember(String fname, String lname, Date dob, Location location)
      Called to remove a member from the database. If the member is not in the database then the user will be notified. If the member is in the database then the member will be checked out of all fitness classes too.
      Parameters:
      fname - the member's first name.
      lname - the member's last name.
      dob - the member's date of birth.
      location - the member's gym location.

    • checkDate

      private boolean checkDate(Date dob)
      Tests the date for today/future date and if the date is 18 years or older.
      Parameters:
      dob - Date of birth to be tested.
      Returns:
      true if the date passed the tests; false otherwise.

    • checkMissingFieldsFitnessClass

      Returns:
      true if there are missing fields; false otherwise.

    • checkOutGuest

      private void checkOutGuest()
      Checks out a guest from a fitness class. If member is not in the class or the database nothing will happen.

    • checkOutMember

      private void checkOutMember()
      Checks out a member from a fitness class. If the date of birth input is invalid, member is not checked in, or the class name inputted does not exist the method will return and the user will be notified why.

    • memberLeaveClassResponse

      private void memberLeaveClassResponse(String className, String instructor, String town, Member member)
      Gets the response for when a member tries to leave a class.
      Parameters:
      className - class name of the fitness class.
      instructor - instructor of the fitness class.
      town - town of the fitness class.
      member - member of the fitness class.

    • checkInGuest

      private void checkInGuest()
      Checks in a guest to a fitness class. Prints success or failure to join class reason.

    • guestCheckOutError

      private boolean guestCheckOutError(Member member)
      Checks for a problem checking out a guest from a fitness class.
      Parameters:
      member - Parent member for the guest.
      Returns:
      true if there was an error; false otherwise.

    • memberExists

      private Member memberExists(Member member)
      Checks if member exists in the database.
      Parameters:
      member - Member to check if exists.
      Returns:
      the Member that exists; null if member is not present.

    • checkInMember

      private void checkInMember()
      Checks in a member to a fitness class. If the date of birth input is invalid, the member does not exist, the member's expiration date is expired, or class name inputted does not exist the method will return and the user will be notified why.

    • getMemberJoinClassResponse

      private void getMemberJoinClassResponse(String className, String instructor, String town, Member member)
      Called to add a member to a fitness class given they meet all the qualifications to. This class will display a string based on whether the member was able to join the class.
      Parameters:
      member - member that is requested to be checked in.
      className - class name the member wishes to join.
      town - town of the gym location.
      instructor - instructor of the class. message

    • isTimeConflict

      private boolean isTimeConflict(Member member, FitnessClass newClass)
      Determines if there is a time conflict for a member joining a class. There is a time conflict if the member is checked into another fitness class that happens during the same time slot.
      Parameters:
      member - Member to be evaluated.
      newClass - fitness class the member wishes to join.
      Returns:
      true if there is a time conflict; false otherwise.

    • addMember

      private void addMember(String fname, String lname, Date dob, String loc)
      Called to add a member to the database. The method will return and print the reason for terminating; Otherwise, the member will be added to the database.
      Parameters:
      fname - the member's first name.
      lname - the member's last name.
      dob - the member's date of birth.
      loc - the member's gym location.

    • isEighteenOrOlder

      private boolean isEighteenOrOlder(Date dob, Date now)
      Used to determine if the date of birth of a member is 18 years or older.
      Parameters:
      dob - a Date object that represents the date of birth of a member.
      now - a Date object that represents the current date.
      Returns:
      true if the date of birth is 18 years or older; false otherwise.
